bgm.name: ダンジョン ・やや緊張感

parameters.name: ダンジョン ・やや緊張感

parameters:
\n<Roselitte>"...Answer my question. You have been conducting financial
transactions with the lord of Anatos, and this cave leads to
Anatos, correct?"

\n<Bandit Leader>"Why do you... Ah, I see, that's what this is about. Your
goal was to head to Anatos from here."

\n<Bandit Leader>"...That's right. Just as you said. This place was
originally a route created by the empire during the old
war."

\n<Bandit Leader>"We got a bit of money for this place and sold the stuff we
stole elsewhere. It was a pretty sweet deal."

\n<Bandit Leader>"Deorc-san was always grumbling about not liking it. Even
though we got money, he hated being bossed around."

\n<Roselitte>"...So his attack on Anatos was revenge for being exploited
all this time... is that it?"
\n<Bandit Leader>"Who knows. I wouldn't know unless I asked him."

\n<Bandit Leader>"...Sigh. Things were going pretty well until that slave
trader bastard showed up and everything went to hell."

\n<Bandit Leader>"Deorc-san is up to something crazy, and the slave trader
bastard hasn't come back... We're really finished now, huh."

\n<Roselitte>"...I have no sympathy for you. It's your own fault for
getting involved in thievery in the first place."

\n<Bandit Leader>"Yeah, really... Ah-ah! I did think about living a better
life though!"
\n<Bandit Leader>"...Huh? What, you're not going to kill me?"

\n<Bandit Leader>"That would be... just keep going forward, and once you
leave the cave, follow the river. You shouldn't get lost."

\n<Roselitte>"Once this matter is settled, I will rectify this region.
Until then, give some thought to that better way of living
you mentioned."
\n<Bandit Leader>"...What is it, Sister? Do you need something?"
\n<Ameria>"...Just stay still for a moment, okay?"

\n<Ameria>"...It's not exactly commendable, but at least you didn't
attack the village during this commotion."
\n<Ameria>"I can't see everything you've done as entirely bad."

\n<Ameria>"Once you've calmed down, please come to the church. The
church welcomes everyone, and God listens to anyone."

\n<Ameria>"I'm in a hurry so I can't treat everyone... but I'll leave
some medicine here, make sure to use it properly for
treatment."
